ural landscape in this era. It is a one-of-a-kind account of one of the most exhilarating and inventive periods for art and culture in New York City’s history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAvant-garde (Music)zNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy20th century. 0aMusiczNew York (State)zNew Yorky20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMusiciansvInterviews. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074967040uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/went2108840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231558631423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231558631/original  a978-3-11-074967-0  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles